            "textpurpose":"Didactics",
            "textentryhtml":"Round, 4.45 cm. diam. gold, slightly younger-than-middle-aged Mao, smiling and showing teeth, facing ¾ frontal to the right; Mao’s jacket collar is open, shirt collar with 1 part tucked in, 1 out (of sweater?). Mao floats against a plain orange-ish ground, encircled by highly geometricized sheathes of wheat (there is a .3 cm. w. space between the badge edge and the wheat circle); Scene at bottom shows figure (PLA soldier? Gender unclear) sitting frontally with right hand turning a spinning wheel, left hand held up.  Inscription to right: “自力更生”.\r\nBack: large oval indentation, clasp at 10 & 2; running script inscription below indentation: “毛主席万岁”.  Molded image of battleship below inscription.\r\n",
